The future will not just judge us by the words we use, or promises we make, but through our actions. [9/9]

This was a tweet-friendly thread of my letter to the #LettersToTheEarth campaign. Find out more at https://t.co/YuQ5U1eDL4 @letterstoearth_

So, in the end, we ask our politicians and industry leaders to please put the world beyond their shareholders and personal interests, and to put the welfare of the developing world beyond petty Realpolitik and fears of being overtaken by our neighbours. [8/9] #LettersToTheEarth
We cannot see it as an us vs. them situation. We must all work together, and we cannot forget our own privelage in this. [7/9] #LettersToTheEarth

We must, as the more wealthy countries, generously give our time, money and resources to build the ecologically friendly industries that the developing world needs to be able to thrive. [6/9] #LettersToTheEarth

But I feel that this must be a global thing, and it would be very hypocritical of us to ask our neigbouring countries to stop using fossil fuels when we got rich off the back of them, when we didn't know better (and then later, when we did). [5/9] #LettersToTheEarth

In a world where many accuse others of 'virtue signalling' to avoid having to do anything, it is heartening to see some large businesses waking up to the importance of ecology. [4/9] #LettersToTheEarth

But there is only so much that one person can do. We can see from research that it will take governments and industry to buy into these projects, to spearhead them and to take them seriously. [3/9] #LettersToTheEarth

I believe that humans have been tasked to look after our natural world, and I wish that people would understand that. To sit idly and wait for a miracle is, in the end, either presumptuous or silly. [2/9] #LettersToTheEarth

It still upsets me that so many people are willing to let our planet slowly die, feeling that it is not their place to help. Either assuming that things will get better without them, or that they have better things to be getting on with. [1/9] #LettersToTheEarth
